values: I am literally addicted to Pinterest. It's worse than cigarettes or coffee ahha. CAN'T STOP! And it's soooo satisfying.
I'm going to start working out again. IT FEELS SOOOO GOOD!

I need to have a good cry. It's not that I'm sad or anything, I just feel like everyone should just have a good, solid cry every so often. And it's been long for me. I feel like I'm holding something in, or something. And I really just want to cry!!! Not even like crying at Titanic. That doesn't count. Hmm!

I almost threw out all my clothes (or rather donated them) today...so tempting. I either need to do that or get over getting rid of clothes that have sentimental value. Half the t-shirts I have, I haven't worn in over a year or maybe even up to five years...aaah! It's kind of overwhelming!

Same with everything else in my room. I have so much random stuff and I want to get rid of all of it but I can't do it at once cause it really is hard! One day/week at a time and I should be fine. I'll just focus on different drawers, etc...

A lot of this inspiration came from this website Pinterest I've been obsessed over lately. 


Really want to make room for those pretty things :) All of which I can find on that website. The website makes me excited to have my own home. 

I feel so excited and happy right now. Life is good and autumn is almost here...

I need to decide if I should take out student loans and finish college in 2 semesters, or take one class for the next 2 semesters and get out of college loan free. Hmmm. I think I would go crazy taking only one class but I don't know...not having any debt sounds pretty great too.

I'm starting to think about my future more and it's kind of scaring me. I have no idea what I'm going to do. But I feel like I'm almost ready to get a move on and grow up a little...!?

And not having a job for two months is just killing me. Coming back from vacation is even worse. I have NO motivation, and the thought of starting this whole job search all over again is making me very anxious. I can't wait for a hook-up like I have with all my other jobs. Waiting doesn't work! Well, I guess it actually does sometimes haha.

Anyway, I'm over the summer hotness. Definitely not helping with my laziness. Fall can come anytime it wants...
Heart, mind & soul crazy for this boy! :D

It's very rare that someone truly pisses me off. But when they do...WATCH OUT!

People been pissing me off left and right lately. My patience has been running short!

So much going through my head right now.  I'm wondering if I'm feeling burnt out? Wishing for a change in scenery for a while, that would be nice. No motivation to be motivated. I need a new job but just hoping my connections can help me with that. And wondering what it is with boys...

Seriously never thought I'd say this but I'm sad I missed the Royal Wedding haha. Just seeing the pictures and videos...it really is exciting and I'm not sure why but I want to say inspiring. Kate looked absolutley beautiful, I can't think of any women ever looking more stunning! Anyway...
I think I want to take up yoga this summer. I'm tired of being sore and stiff all the time. Ha ha. Plus I need to find a form of relaxation. Yes...I think I shall.
They say you can learn from your mistakes. Which is true. But I find that I tend to keep making those mistakes...and it makes me feel like a fool. Stupid boys. Silly me.
Alright. Seriously. I need a break from going out so much. Starting soon...haha. I'm going to hibernate. I need to stop drinking. I need to stop making a fucking fool out of myself. SERIOUSLY
I see why people love deadmau5 so much. I'm obsessed right now...

I am very relieved to know this semester will probably have been my hardest. I only need to take 9 credits for my last two semesters and so far I'll have Tuesday and Thursdays off next semester. I'll be able to work a lot more and save up money for travels! Also fairly excited to look at internships for Summer 2012. They will be a very good glimpse into the work I can do as an Anthropologist. I'm starting to feel a lot more optimistic about my future now. And one of my friends told me I definitely was an Anthropologist and this just made me really happy. I really love my major!

In the meantime, I need to find more time for school. There are only 5 weeks or something left. I still have 5 papers left and finals, and lots of readings. I need to drop a shift at work and limit my nights of going out. I'm afraid I won't have a lot of money going into the summer...and if I stay at Corbett I'll only get paid once in June. Don't know what I'm going to do about that yet. I am so conflicted in getting a new job over the summer, just cause I'm worried about flexibility of trading/dropping shifts. Oh well, I'll deal with that when the time comes.

Janie got back from Paris yesterday and I CANNOT wait to go. It is so beautiful. So rich in history. When I make it over to Europe definitely need to stay a few weeks. So much to see and do. Janie brought back some wonderful gifts, very generous. :)

On top of everything else, BASEBALL is here!!! And we all know this makes Jenna a very happy person.

Time for homework...and some fancy scientific research!

I'm so excited for so many things...it is slightly overwhelming! Then again knowing me, I couldn't have it any other way. I have so much to look forward to, so many rewards in store. Getting there is still half the fun :)

Oh dear god it truly is scary how the girls who should NOT be having babies young or if ever, are having babies young. It continues the cycle and it's so sad and pathetic! Ahhh what can we do about this problem?! They are usually the ones in terrible relationships as well, so the baby is going to grow up influenced by its fucked up parents (take Sarah). And this young 19 year old I used to work with...oh my gosh it's just so sad!

Seriously you'd think by now that they'd come out for some instant cure for sore throats. But nooo...NOTHING I've taken works, not even a pain pill. Not aleve, not advil, not syrup, not spray, not lozenges...NOTHING. It is so miserable...waking up throughout the night when you have to swallow. Not being able to drink water because it hurts so bad. On the bright side, sure as hell not smoking any cigarettes with my throat hurting this bad. 

Don't share drinks with people. Just don't. I shared drinks with about 10 different people this week I realize and NEVER will do that again. I feel so disgusted ha ha

Being sick over spring break....PERFECT! At least I can try really hard to get some more work done...maybe

Reminder to myself: Talk to financial aid person when I get back from break!!! And get a new job during the summer :( Why does this all seem so hard? Also, I was going to try to apply for student trainer at my work but fucking forgot and missed the deadline...

I am such a good student. I work really hard and get good grades but I don't quite understand what it's for. It doesn't seem like it's going to get me anywhere. If I have such a hard time finding motivation to get a good job that pays well...what is that going to mean down the road? 

I worry way too much sometimes...but then again I have reason to. I need help! Like a life coach or something. I feel kind of helpless and hopeless about all of this, though I know there's no reason to feel that way.
Never, never depend on one person for your happiness. Whether it be a friend or a significant other. You never know what will happen. They may change and leave you feeling left behind.
I just wanna be able to travel. Everywhere. Easily, and for cheap. And on my own time. I have some things here in the States that I cannot miss.

When I have kids, I'm not letting them get a cell phone until they are 15, nor will I let them get a Facebook page until then. Haha. It's so disturbing to see girls who look like they are under 10 texting away on a cell phone, same goes for 10 year old kids having a Facebook. The line should be drawn somewhere, right?

Oh my goodness I just checked my old e-mail (justsh00tme@hotmail.com) and it has a butt load of saved conversations from AIM and surveys and E-MAILS when we actually still used them. All the drama of 9th grade and what not. So funny! What little kids we were!

I hate drama. I really, really hate drama. I avoid it as best as I can. I avoid confrontations as best as I can too, sometimes that may mean ignoring the person. Is that so wrong? I just like to wait til things blow over...and they usually do. 

This weekend has been filled with drama so far. Pathetic. And really annoying.

I really just want to be left alone sometimes! People don't understand that. Besides those who feel the same way as I do with drama and confrontations.
A few hours after I'm done for the semester and I already feel like I'm in a funk. Maybe it is just the mood of the day...but NOTHING sounds appealing. I HATE this feeling!
i really wish i was a witch. somethings i wish i could obliviate. plus i am just so in love with harry potter ♥

I've been dreaming about my first love nearly every night for some time now. And thinking about it too. Why? It's so strange, I want to be single, but maybe I'm just craving that level of feelings for someone again. Or maybe I just miss him.

I realize I am a overall very happy person.

When I think about it, the only things that really get me down are school sometimes, when I feel overwhelmed. And playing with my hair. I will find myself in class (sometimes) sititng there the whole period and I CAN'T for the life of me stop. This sounds so dumb but it really is to me a nasty nasty habit that I can't break and I get so sad sometimes about it.

But, sometimes something as simple as a quote can really help my outlook: 

Instead of obsessing over the problems, you can be working on the solutions.

I don't want to be one of those cheesey "I AM SO IN LOVE WITH LIFE!" people but it feels good sometimes. And I like this website...www.greatday.com...just thought I'd share it with you guys :)

i hate my stupid car :(

the damage that was done to it would cost more to repair than what my car is worth apparently. so i'm going to get a check for however much that is, which apparently won't be very much at all. and i probably have to use all of that to repair all the other shit that's wrong with my car. so i'd be stuck with my car that looks horrible, but i also know shit is just going to keep breaking. i really don't want to keep it. it's really not worth it.

if i lived closer to campus i would just get a bike, honestly. but i can't bike to home and campus so much for work and school, and i especially won't be able to once winter starts. 

i know i can take the bus, and i know people have it worse than me but that doesn't make it any easier on me since its such a sudden change that's gonna be really hard to adjust to in the time that i won't have my car, or if i just get rid of it. 

shitty shitty shitty

i love having nights that just are so fucking fun you can't stop thinking about it. juno what has been that for me three times now...great times. and at hodi's...i wish hodi's would have more good shows like that!!!

mmm...

cassidy wright is sooo damn good looking. i haven't seen or thought about him for a couple weeks, but then all of a sudden i was randomly reminded. 

oooooh cassidy. ha ha ha.

Once again feeling down about things that I could and should change...I am extremely lacking in motivation and drive. I am not a go getter. And it's terribly depressing. And I really don't like school. I hate school.

I wish I could experience fall in the East Coast. Soon, very soon.

I'm amping up my traveling dreams again, I believe my classes have re-motivated me. But I also need to be patient and actually work really hard towards saving money. It's a slow process but I feel I'm moving in the right direction.
I know what I'm going to be for Halloween...

Holy crap, last week really kicked my ass! I'm sick now :( Of course I would be. The transition from not working or doing anything a month to school and work was kinda tough. I was so tired all week! It's gonna be hard not going out as much haha but it'll be good for me...

i feel...done. i don't even know what that means. i just need freshness. aaaaahhhh and it's all about to start over again!!! and i feel already that it's going nowhere. it's for nothing. hopefully i'll prove that wrong.

Let me just start off my saying I hate Katy Perry. She looks like a retard and her head is a little too long for her good and she says stupid shit like "Lady Gaga's "Alejandro" video is blasphemous." I really, really hate her, I don't know why she bothers me so much. 

Second, I'm in a piss ass mood because my aunt has been around the last few days and I like her and all but it's annoying. She is sleeping in Janie's room and that means Janie gets my room. I usually slept over at Skyler's but for some reason he hasn't talked to me the last two days at all so I've been sleeping on the couch, then in my parents room. I don't know if I should have a boyfriend because I become dependent on them pretty quickly. Should I be as bummed as I am that he hasn't talked to me in two days?

And I have a KILLER headache and I'm just feeling super pissed right now. I'm not meeting any of my expectations in life but for the life of me I don't have it in me to try. It's pathetic and I really have no excuse for it. And it's a cycle. The more I think about it the more I get down on myself and the more my motivation goes down the drain. 

And I'm broke. And Kendra is gone. 

FML.
So stressed. Life has been kicking me in the ass these last few days. Everthing has caught up to me...fuck :(

what a fun birthday week :)

i love my peoples.

vacation in less than one week! ♥

i am SOOO excited. i NEEED this so bad! nice relaxing fun time with the family. no facebook. no phone (mostly.) it will be amazing and hopefully help motivate me for all the shit i need to take care of when i get back.

and turning the big 22 this week...leandra you should come to the aggie for a while for a free reggae show. i'd love to see you!

i have a feeling when school comes around i'm gonna go into hermitish mode. with nick and kendra being gone i don't foresee going out as much. but whatever...it wouldn't hurt to really concentrate on school as it is time to get serious. and focus on a job so i can make money. we will see how it plays out. i'm honestly starting to get excited for fall for whatever reason...

I fucking love the Mishawaka. And The Motet. They honestly KILLED it last night, they are so fucking good! So much fun. 

I still haven't done a lot of the things I'd like to do this summer, but it's definitely been the funnest summer I've had. Good shows, good people, good times.
I suddenly have this overwhelming desire to be with a tall guy. Yeah, it's driving me crazy.

i need a new job so bad :( i've wasted a year and a half at this stupid job that's not giving me any hours and low pay. i owe people money and i'm gonna be broke by the end of july...i don't know if i can even afford the mile high music festival right now. i need to get my shit together! this is not cool anymore, i'm 21 years old and should have money saved up! so mad at myself right now :(

sonic bloom was fuuuun! though i wish i would have been a lot more high.....hahah. loved seeing my ladies down there :)

i can't wait to have some days off from work...even though i only work 3 hours it interupts the day. i really need to get on doing more summery shit!

Wow...I looove Denver. I had such a blast at Quixote's last night. That place is fucking sick! There were three bands going at once and it was like a mini music festival haha. There was an outdoor patio where people were playing and it was like a mini Mishawaka or something haha. I enjoyed all the bands and all the people. There were many very entertaining people, which I probably noticed a lot more cause I was actually sober! If I weren't in college...I'd definitely move down there. So much going on...so much fun. And The Nu Classics...killed it! I love them :) Such a good summer so far! Still sooo much to do. And only 2 months to do it...

This summer might just officially be the greatest ever. Still got Soulive next week to look forward, Red Sox game, The Motet and Lotus at the Mish, California, Lady Gaga, Cubbies games and if I can volunteer for the Telluride Jazz Fest I can get into that free and possibly get free Phish tix as well...if not, some guy offered me free tix if I help set up tents before the show. And then after that is the Mile High Music Fest. That would be one solid week of craziness...

But other than that I still need to hike! And camp. And still get my bike fixed...oy.

On another note...Hodi's is turning whack on me. I think I might start limiting it to shows I definitely want to see and Monday nights. Ha. It just sucks because that was the place I always felt most comfortable and that is starting to not be so true. Not just because of the people who go there, but the people who work there are kinda crazy...

I'm having a lot of fun right now but I can't wait to get out of Fort Collins for a solid week. And then whenever I move or get out and travel. I NEED TO TRAVEL! New choicest destination is Thailand...ah!
one of my favorite bands is playing a free show in vail on the 15th...i am so. excited.
